citation: Proclamation under the Living Marine Miscellaneous Amendments (Digital Processes) Act 2021 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Living Marine Miscellaneous Amendments (Digital Processes) Act 2021

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Living Marine Miscellaneous Amendments (Digital Processes) Act 2021 fix 31 March 2023 as the day on which the provisions of that Act commence.

27 March 2023

B. BAKER

Governor

By Her Excellency's Command,

JO PALMER

Minister for Primary Industries and Water

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 28 March 2023

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Natural Resources and Environment Tasmania.
